descriptionNullable: The dataset contains images of 32 Indian mangoes leaf species. These varieties are separated from each others on the basis of their features. These usually feature such as texture, shape, and color. With these features that different mangoes verities, it is possible to classify. The dataset contains 768 images of 32 Mango Leaf Species (Indian) and each species has 24 images from different angles and orientations. In this research, 'Alphanso', 'Amarpali', 'Amarpali 13_1', 'Amarpali 4_9', 'Amarpali Desi', 'Ambika', 'Austin', 'Chausa 13_1', 'Chausa Desi','Dasheri Desi','Dasherion 13_1', 'Dusheri4_9', 'Duthpedha', 'Farnadeen', 'Kent', 'Keshar', 'Langra Desi', 'Langra 13_1', 'Langra 4_9', 'Lilly', 'Mallika', 'Neelam', 'Pamar','Pusa Lalima', 'Pusa Peetamber', 'Pusa Pratibha', 'Pusa Shresth', 'Pusa Surya', 'Ram Kela Desi', 'Ramkela 13_1', 'Ramkela4_9', 'Ratna' which are 32 Indian Mango Leaf Species were used. Models were created by using the Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) algorithm for the image dataset and the classification successes from the models were achieved 99.09%. The provided dataset can be considered as a benchmark for testing and comparing the performance of different algorithms.
